  "prompt": "What is Intel XDK?",
  "response": "Intel XDK (Cross-Platform Development Kit) was a free integrated development environment (IDE) created by Intel for developing cross-platform mobile and web applications. Here are some key details about Intel XDK:\n\n1. Purpose:\n- Designed to help developers create mobile and web applications\n- Enabled cross-platform development for multiple operating systems and devices\n- Supported HTML5, JavaScript, and hybrid app development\n\n2. Features:\n- Visual designer and code editor\n- Built-in debugging tools\n- Performance analysis and optimization\n- App templates and sample projects\n- Support for multiple platforms (iOS, Android, Windows)\n- Cloud-based build and testing services\n\n3. Target Platforms:\n- Mobile platforms: iOS, Android\n- Web browsers\n- Hybrid mobile applications\n- Intel-based devices\n\n4. Development Approach:\n- Used HTML5, CSS, and JavaScript\n- Supported Apache Cordova/PhoneGap for hybrid app development\n- Enabled developers to create apps using web technologies\n\n5. Status:\n- Intel discontinued active development and support for XDK\n- No longer recommended for new projects\n- Developers are advised to use alternative development tools\n\nAlternative tools that replaced Intel XDK include Apache Cordova, Ionic, React Native, and other cross-platform development frameworks.",
